n=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> I don't think I can properly critique your work or give a rat's ass about your UI without first hand experience of it.  Unlike 99% of the individuals that are having fun making mods you choose to display only screenshots but not share your work.  Pretty pictures are nice and all, but don't be surprised when people think you are just wasting space on the forum by stroking your own ego under the guise of requesting input on how to improve your work.<br>
<br>
Why should we care to help improve your work or even give positive feedback when all it will do is justify you keeping it to yourself?<br>
<br>
I am sure you have helped others in the past or lent them your expertise, this is a decent of you.  However it is a moot point when the subject at hand is something you wish to keep private.  It doesn't help anyone but yourself to come here and post screenshots, list features, go on a long discourse about all of the labor you have put into your UI, and then ask for input from us.  Not only is it a ridiculous request, since we have no ability to have any hands on experience with your UI...it is selfish.<br>
<br>
