<br>
You should try using /viewport if your really concerned about screen reality.  I currently have 240x30px for my target bar covering my visible screen (mostly because as enchanter my target bar being visible is very important, as half the job of an enchnater is aquiring the correct target), this is with 4 chats and every window I could want for any class open.  Everything else is bordering my /viewport area of /view 128 100 1024 768.  Reso 1280x1024.  The formulas for finding what viewport you want is [X1] = ([Reso X] / 2) - ([X2] /2);  [Y1] = [Reso Y] - [Height of stuff on bottom (proy chat bar)] - [Y2].  x1 x2 y1 y2 are in the form /viewport X1 Y1 X2 Y2<br>
<br>
It takes a while to get used to, but now that I've had it for a few weeks it would be almost impossible for me to go back to almost 20% unusable screen, I currently have around 2%(? don't wana do math, this seems about correct) used, but its on bottom 30px of 768 pixels so it's almost never even a consideration as thats mostly ground/area where my char is in topdown, and the target window isn't locked so if I need to I can drag over one of my less important chat windows if I'm ever in need of 100% screen reality.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
Ealarx<br>
